***As ADC Calls for Citizens’ Support For FGN’s Full Implementation of The New Electoral Act ASABA – Chairmen’s Forum of Africa Democratic Congress, ADC under the leadership of Hon. Prince Joe Chukwu has enjoined President Muhammadu Buhari to work towards ensuring that Federal Government of Nigeria implement the new electoral act as amended which stipulates for “early release of Fund to INEC to give room for the Agency’s financial independence.” Our reporter learnt this pen-ultimate weekend in a communique made available to newsmen in Asaba by the Delta State Chairman, African Democratic Congress (ADC), Hon prince Joe Chukwu who urged Nigerians to lend their voices towards strengthening the feats of the new electoral act so as to make progress. The Forum’s statement reads in parts: “The early release of electoral funds will strengthen INEC financial independence. The amendment act bill as passed and signed will help to raise the quality of Nigeria’s democracy. It will ensure that the country’s leadership recruitment process is rested on a credible and transparent electoral framework.” “Also, the inclusion of electronic transmission of result, power to review Election results declared under duress, political neutrality of INEC Personnel, and legalization of electronic accreditation of voters are other benefits of the new electoral act.” “Others worthy of mention are: Inclusion of persons with Disability, using accredited votes to determine total votes, early conduct of Party primaries, elongation of campaign period before election and substitution of candidate in the event of death in an election will help to inject sanity and credibility in our electoral process”. “We call on all stakeholders to vigorously and honestly work for the full implementation of this act in our forthcoming General election in 2023”.